messages.message:
The file picker doesn’t work, it assumes that ‘repo/picker_utils’ is a file path and redirects request to core-platform, can reproduce on aihub-sandbox

```owner@dev:~$ cs logs -f core-platform
✔ select the only one - DAEMON:core-platform@instabase
2025/04/02 21:52:31 ERROR coreplatformservice/repo/handler/repo.go:212 -- Fail: Repo (repo/picker_utils) not found. Err: code = NOT_FOUND, msg = Not found, wrappedErr = sql: no rows in result set
2025/04/02 21:52:31 ERROR coreplatformservice/account/handler/preference.go:478 -- Preference does not exist
2025/04/02 21:52:31 ERROR coreplatformservice/account/handler/preference.go:478 -- Preference does not exist
2025/04/02 21:52:31 ERROR coreplatformservice/account/handler/preference.go:478 -- Preference does not exist
2025/04/02 21:52:31 ERROR coreplatformservice/account/handler/preference.go:478 -- Preference does not exist```
@Jessica could you take a look? Maybe something to do with how we truncate the drive name from the file path?
I merged a fix for this a couple hours ago!
This just affected the one on the legacy platform btw - a bug from when I replaced ajax requests with fetch requests: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/69416
